./  ADD  SSI=90400232,NAME=IKTCAS54
         TITLE '*** IKTCAS54 - PARAMETER PROCESSOR SCANNER'             00001000
IKTCAS54 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00002000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00003000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00004000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00005000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00006000
         DC    C'IKTCAS54  79.040'                                 0001 00007000
         DROP  @15                                                      00008000
@PROLOG  ST    @14,12(,@13)                                        0001 00009000
         STM   @00,@12,20(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  LA    @08,4095(,@12)                                      0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00013000
         USING @PSTART+4095,@08                                    0001 00014000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0001 00015000
         GETMAIN  R,LV=(0)                                              00016000
         LR    @10,@01                                             0001 00017000
         USING @DATD,@10                                           0001 00018000
         ST    @13,@SA00001+4                                      0001 00019000
         LM    @00,@01,20(@13)                                     0001 00020000
         ST    @10,8(,@13)                                         0001 00021000
         LR    @13,@10                                             0001 00022000
         EJECT                                                          00023000
*                                                                  0119 00024000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00025000
*/*                                                                  */ 00026000
*/*    THIS PROGRAM IS ORGANIZED AS FOLLOWS:                         */ 00027000
*/*                                                                  */ 00028000
*/*        A - HOUSEKEEPING                                          */ 00029000
*/*                                                                  */ 00030000
*/*        B - MAINLINE, WHICH CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING:            */ 00031000
*/*            1)  IF DATA IS IN A CIB, MOVE IT INTO A WORK BUFFER   */ 00032000
*/*                AND RELEASE THE CIB WITH THE QEDIT MACRO          */ 00033000
*/*            2)  VALIDITY CHECKING OF INPUT OPTIONS.  IF ANY       */ 00034000
*/*                INCONSISTENCIES ARE FOUND, TERMINATE WITH A RETURN*/ 00035000
*/*                CODE OF 4.                                        */ 00036000
*/*            3)  SCAN PARAMETERS, FROM EITHER A DATA OR WORK       */ 00037000
*/*                BUFFER.                                           */ 00038000
*/*            4)  IF PARAMETERS FROM A PARMLIB ARE DESIRED, READ IN */ 00039000
*/*                THE DESIRED MEMBER AND PROCESS ITS PARAMETERS.    */ 00040000
*/*            5)  IF NECESSARY, OVERLAY MEMBER PARAMETERS WITH      */ 00041000
*/*                BUFFER PARAMETERS.                                */ 00042000
*/*            6)  IF REQUESTED, UPDATE TCAS TABLE                   */ 00043000
*/*            7)  IF REQUESTED, WRITE OUT PARAMETERS                */ 00044000
*/*                                                                  */ 00045000
*/*        C - CLEANUP AND RETURN                                    */ 00046000
*/*                                                                  */ 00047000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00048000
*                                                                  0119 00049000
*   SCANERR='0'B;                   /* INITIALIZE SW                 */ 00050000
*   GOSW1='1'B;                     /* INITIALIZE SW                 */ 00051000
         OI    GOSW1,B'00100000'                                   0120 00052000
         NI    SCANERR,B'01111111'                                 0120 00053000
*   PRNTPTR=ADDR(PRNTDAT5);         /* 1ST CHAR IN PRINT LINE        */ 00054000
         LA    PRNTPTR,PRNTDAT5                                    0121 00055000
*   PRNTEND=PRNTPTR+67;             /* LAST CHAR IN PRINT LINE       */ 00056000
         LA    @15,67                                              0122 00057000
         ALR   @15,PRNTPTR                                         0122 00058000
         ST    @15,PRNTEND                                         0122 00059000
*   SYNADSW1='N';                   /* INITIALIZE                    */ 00060000
         MVI   SYNADSW1,C'N'                                       0123 00061000
*   SYNADSW2='N';                   /* ERROR                         */ 00062000
         MVI   SYNADSW2,C'N'                                       0124 00063000
*   DCBABSW1='N';                   /* HANDLING                      */ 00064000
         MVI   DCBABSW1,C'N'                                       0125 00065000
*   DCBABSW2='N';                   /* SWITCHES                      */ 00066000
         MVI   DCBABSW2,C'N'                                       0126 00067000
*   CALL CHKOPTNS;                  /* CHECK INPUT OPTIONS, ETC      */ 00068000
         BAL   @14,CHKOPTNS                                        0127 00069000
*   IF MLPMINV='1'B THEN            /* ERRORS                        */ 00070000
         TM    MLPMINV(MLPMPTR),B'01000000'                        0128 00071000
         BNO   @RF00128                                            0128 00072000
*     RTNCODE=4;                    /* YES - NON-ZERO RTN CODE       */ 00073000
         MVC   RTNCODE(2),@CH00063                                 0129 00074000
*   ELSE                                                           0130 00075000
*     DO;                           /* NO - CONTINUE ON WITH         */ 00076000
         B     @RC00128                                            0130 00077000
@RF00128 DS    0H                                                  0131 00078000
*       RTNCODE=0;                  /* ZERO RETURN CODE              */ 00079000
         SLR   @02,@02                                             0131 00080000
         STH   @02,RTNCODE                                         0131 00081000
*       CALL SCANPARM;              /* SCAN BUFFER PARAMETERS        */ 00082000
         BAL   @14,SCANPARM                                        0132 00083000
*       IF MLPMINV='0'B THEN        /* ALL THE PARMS OK              */ 00084000
         TM    MLPMINV(MLPMPTR),B'01000000'                        0133 00085000
         BNZ   @RF00133                                            0133 00086000
*         DO;                       /* YES - CONTINUE ON             */ 00087000
*           CALL READMBR;           /* READ AND PROCESS PARMLIB      */ 00088000
         BAL   @14,READMBR                                         0135 00089000
*           CALL OVERLAY;           /* MERGE PARMS                   */ 00090000
         BAL   @14,OVERLAY                                         0136 00091000
*           CALL TCASUPDT;          /* UPDATE TCAS TABLE PARMS       */ 00092000
         BAL   @14,TCASUPDT                                        0137 00093000
*           CALL WRITEOUT;          /* PRINT TCAS TABLE PARMS        */ 00094000
         BAL   @14,WRITEOUT                                        0138 00095000
*         END;                                                     0139 00096000
*       ELSE                        /* NO - ERROR FOUND              */ 00097000
*         IF PRINTSW='1'B THEN      /* DOING A PRINTOUT              */ 00098000
         B     @RC00133                                            0140 00099000
@RF00133 TM    PRINTSW,B'00001000'                                 0140 00100000
         BNO   @RF00140                                            0140 00101000
*           DO;                     /* YES                           */ 00102000
*             GEN(CLOSE PRINTOUT)   /* CLOSE PRINTOUT                */ 00103000
*             REFS(R0,R1,R14,R15,PRINTOUT);                        0142 00104000
         CLOSE PRINTOUT                                                 00105000
*           END;                                                   0143 00106000
*     END;                                                         0144 00107000
@RF00140 DS    0H                                                  0144 00108000
@RC00133 DS    0H                                                  0145 00109000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0145 00110000
*    (R15) RESTRICTED;                                             0145 00111000
@RC00128 DS    0H                                                  0146 00112000
*   R15=RTNCODE;                    /* INSERT RETURN CODE            */ 00113000
         LH    R15,RTNCODE                                         0146 00114000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0147 00115000
*    (R15) UNRESTRICTED;                                           0147 00116000
*   RETURN;                         /* FINISHED                      */ 00117000
@EL00001 L     @13,4(,@13)                                         0148 00118000
@EF00001 L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0148 00119000
         LR    @01,@10                                             0148 00120000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00121000
@ER00001 L     @14,12(,@13)                                        0148 00122000
         LM    @00,@12,20(@13)                                     0148 00123000
         BR    @14                                                 0148 00124000
         EJECT                                                          00125000
*CHKOPTNS:                                                         0149 00126000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0149 00127000
CHKOPTNS ST    @14,@SA00002                                        0149 00128000
*                                                                  0150 00129000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00130000
*/*                                                                  */ 00131000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE DOES THREE THINGS:                            */ 00132000
*/*                                                                  */ 00133000
*/*    -   IF PARAMETERS ARE IN A CIB BUFFER, MOVE THEM INTO A WORK  */ 00134000
*/*        BUFFER AND FREE THE CIB BUFFER                            */ 00135000
*/*    -   MAKE SURE THE INPUT OPTIONS ARE CONSISTENT.               */ 00136000
*/*    -   IF A PRINTOUT WANTED, OPEN THE PRINTOUT DCB               */ 00137000
*/*                                                                  */ 00138000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00139000
*                                                                  0150 00140000
*   CIBUFFER='';                    /* CLEAR WORK BUFFER             */ 00141000
         MVI   CIBUFFER,C' '                                       0150 00142000
         MVC   CIBUFFER+1(47),CIBUFFER                             0150 00143000
*   IF MLPMCIB='0'B|MLPMSCA=0 THEN                                 0151 00144000
         TM    MLPMCIB(MLPMPTR),B'00000001'                        0151 00145000
         BZ    @RT00151                                            0151 00146000
         L     @15,MLPMSCA(,MLPMPTR)                               0151 00147000
         LTR   @15,@15                                             0151 00148000
         BZ    @RT00151                                            0151 00149000
*     ;                             /* SKIP IF NO CIB BUFFER         */ 00150000
*   ELSE                            /* A CIB BUFFER                  */ 00151000
*     DO;                           /* YES                           */ 00152000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0154 00153000
*        (CIBNAME)                  /* SET UP NEW BASE FOR CIB       */ 00154000
*             BASED(MLPMSCA);                                      0154 00155000
*       IF CIBDATLN>0 THEN          /* IF DATA, MOVE INTO            */ 00156000
         L     @15,MLPMSCA(,MLPMPTR)                               0155 00157000
         LH    @14,CIBDATLN(,@15)                                  0155 00158000
         LTR   @14,@14                                             0155 00159000
         BNP   @RF00155                                            0155 00160000
*         MVC(CIBUFFER(1:CIBDATLN),CIBDATA);/* WORK BUFFER           */ 00161000
         L     @01,MLPMSCA(,MLPMPTR)                               0156 00162000
         LH    @14,CIBDATLN(,@01)                                  0156 00163000
         BCTR  @14,0                                               0156 00164000
         EX    @14,@SM01645                                        0156 00165000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0157 00166000
*        (CIBNAME);                 /* REVERT TO OLD BASE            */ 00167000
@RF00155 DS    0H                                                  0158 00168000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0158 00169000
*        (R2,                                                      0158 00170000
*         R3) RESTRICTED;                                          0158 00171000
*       R2=ADDR(CHCIBP);            /* ADDR OF CIB PTR               */ 00172000
         L     R2,CSCBPTR(,TWAPTR)                                 0159 00173000
         LA    R2,CHCIBP(,R2)                                      0159 00174000
*       R3=MLPMSCA;                 /* ADDR OF CIB TO BE FREED       */ 00175000
         L     R3,MLPMSCA(,MLPMPTR)                                0160 00176000
*       GEN(QEDIT ORIGIN=(R2),BLOCK=(R3))/* FREE CIB                 */ 00177000
*       REFS(R0,R1,R2,R3,R14,R15);                                 0161 00178000
         QEDIT ORIGIN=(R2),BLOCK=(R3)                                   00179000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0162 00180000
*        (R2,                                                      0162 00181000
*         R3) UNRESTRICTED;                                        0162 00182000
*     END;                                                         0163 00183000
*   IF MLPMFL1='00'X|               /* CHECK                         */ 00184000
*       (MLPMBUF='1'B&MLPMCIB='1'B) /* OBVIOUS                       */ 00185000
*     THEN                                                         0164 00186000
@RT00151 CLI   MLPMFL1(MLPMPTR),X'00'                              0164 00187000
         BE    @RT00164                                            0164 00188000
         TM    MLPMBUF(MLPMPTR),B'00000011'                        0164 00189000
         BNO   @RF00164                                            0164 00190000
@RT00164 DS    0H                                                  0165 00191000
*     DO;                           /* INPUT                         */ 00192000
*       MLPMINV='1'B;               /* ERRORS                        */ 00193000
         OI    MLPMINV(MLPMPTR),B'01000000'                        0166 00194000
*       RETURN;                     /* .                             */ 00195000
@EL00002 DS    0H                                                  0167 00196000
@EF00002 DS    0H                                                  0167 00197000
@ER00002 L     @14,@SA00002                                        0167 00198000
         BR    @14                                                 0167 00199000
*     END;                          /* .                             */ 00200000
*   IF MLPMWPM='1'B THEN            /* PRINTOUT WANTED               */ 00201000
@RF00164 TM    MLPMWPM(MLPMPTR),B'00010000'                        0169 00202000
         BNO   @RF00169                                            0169 00203000
*     DO;                           /* YES                           */ 00204000
*       GEN(OPEN  (PRINTOUT,OUTPUT))                               0171 00205000
*       REFS(R0,R1,R14,R15,PRINTOUT);                              0171 00206000
         OPEN  (PRINTOUT,OUTPUT)                                        00207000
*       DCBPTR=ADDR(PRINTOUT);      /* SETUP PTR                     */ 00208000
         LA    DCBPTR,PRINTOUT                                     0172 00209000
*       IF DCBABSW2='Y'|DCBOFOPN='0'B THEN/* GOOD OPEN               */ 00210000
         CLI   DCBABSW2,C'Y'                                       0173 00211000
         BE    @RT00173                                            0173 00212000
         TM    DCBOFOPN+40(DCBPTR),B'00010000'                     0173 00213000
         BNZ   @RF00173                                            0173 00214000
@RT00173 DS    0H                                                  0174 00215000
*         DO;                       /* NO                            */ 00216000
*           RESPECIFY                                              0175 00217000
*            (R1) RESTRICTED;                                      0175 00218000
*           R1=17;                  /* MESSAGE NUMBER                */ 00219000
         LA    R1,17                                               0176 00220000
*           CALL MSGBLK;            /* ADDR OF LIST FORM OF MSG      */ 00221000
         L     @15,TWAMSG(,TWAPTR)                                 0177 00222000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0177 00223000
*           R1=ADDR(IKT017I);       /* ADDR OF LIST FORM             */ 00224000

*GETMBRNM:                                                         0274 00512000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0274 00513000
GETMBRNM ST    @14,12(,@13)                                        0274 00514000
*                                                                  0275 00515000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00516000
*/*                                                                  */ 00517000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE DETERMINES WHAT MEMBER NAME THE OPERATOR      */ 00518000
*/*    WANTS USED IN ACCESSING PARMLIB.                              */ 00519000
*/*                                                                  */ 00520000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00521000
*                                                                  0275 00522000
*   KEYWDNM='MEMBER  ';             /* KEYWORD NAME WANTED           */ 00523000
         MVC   KEYWDNM(8),@CC00329                                 0275 00524000
*   TABLEPTR=ADDR(VERIBUFR);        /* KEYWORD TABLE                 */ 00525000
         LA    TABLEPTR,VERIBUFR                                   0276 00526000
*   DO WHILE(TBLNAMEÂ¬=KEYWDNM);     /* FIND                          */ 00527000
         B     @DE00277                                            0277 00528000
@DL00277 DS    0H                                                  0278 00529000
*     TABLEPTR=TABLEPTR+20;         /* PROPER                        */ 00530000
         AL    TABLEPTR,@CF00144                                   0278 00531000
*   END;                            /* ENTRY                         */ 00532000
@DE00277 CLC   TBLNAME(8,TABLEPTR),KEYWDNM                         0279 00533000
         BNE   @DL00277                                            0279 00534000
*   SAVEPTR=ADDR(SAVEBUFR)+8*(TBLDISP-1);/* ADDR OF WORK AREA        */ 00535000
         LA    SAVEPTR,SAVEBUFR                                    0280 00536000
         LH    @04,TBLDISP(,TABLEPTR)                              0280 00537000
         BCTR  @04,0                                               0280 00538000
         SLA   @04,3                                               0280 00539000
         ALR   SAVEPTR,@04                                         0280 00540000
*   IF SAVECHAR=HEXBC THEN                                         0281 00541000
         CLI   SAVECHAR(SAVEPTR),X'BC'                             0281 00542000
         BE    @RT00281                                            0281 00543000
*     ;                             /* MEMBER= ENTERED NO - USE NAME    00544000
*                                      IN PROC                       */ 00545000
*   ELSE                                                           0283 00546000
*     DO;                           /* YES - GET MEMBER NAME         */ 00547000
*       WORKPARM=SAVAREA;           /* GET NAME ENTERED BY THE     0284 00548000
*                                      OPERATOR IF ITS 2 DIGITS, ADD    00549000
*                                      THEM TO 'MEMDEFLT', ELSE USE     00550000
*                                      THE NAME AS IS                */ 00551000
         MVC   WORKPARM(8),SAVAREA(SAVEPTR)                        0284 00552000
*       IF(WORKPRM(1)>='0'&WORKPRM(1)<='9')&(WORKPRM(2)>='0'&WORKPRM(2) 00553000
*           <='9') THEN                                            0285 00554000
         CLI   WORKPRM,C'0'                                        0285 00555000
         BL    @RF00285                                            0285 00556000
         CLI   WORKPRM,C'9'                                        0285 00557000
         BH    @RF00285                                            0285 00558000
         CLI   WORKPRM+1,C'0'                                      0285 00559000
         BL    @RF00285                                            0285 00560000
         CLI   WORKPRM+1,C'9'                                      0285 00561000
         BH    @RF00285                                            0285 00562000
*         DO;                                                      0286 00563000
*           TSO=MEMDEFLT;                                          0287 00564000
         MVC   TSO(6),@CC00181                                     0287 00565000
*           TSO1=WORKPRM(1);                                       0288 00566000
         MVC   TSO1(1),WORKPRM                                     0288 00567000
*           TSO2=WORKPRM(2);                                       0289 00568000
         MVC   TSO2(1),WORKPRM+1                                   0289 00569000
*           SAVAREA=TSOKEYNN;                                      0290 00570000
         MVC   SAVAREA(8,SAVEPTR),TSOKEYNN                         0290 00571000
*         END;                                                     0291 00572000
*     END;                                                         0292 00573000
*   END GETMBRNM;                                                  0293 00574000
@EL00004 DS    0H                                                  0293 00575000
@EF00004 DS    0H                                                  0293 00576000
@ER00004 L     @14,12(,@13)                                        0293 00577000
         BR    @14                                                 0293 00578000
         EJECT                                                          00579000
*READMBR:                                                          0294 00580000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0294 00581000
READMBR  ST    @14,@SA00005                                        0294 00582000
*                                                                  0295 00583000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00584000
*/*                                                                  */ 00585000
*/*    THE PURPOSE OF THIS SUBROUTINE IS TO READ AND PROCESS THE     */ 00586000
*/*    MEMBER OF PARMLIB WHICH THE OPERATOR WANTS TO USE IN          */ 00587000
*/*    BRINGING UP TCAS.  THE FOLLOWING THINGS ARE DONE:             */ 00588000
*/*                                                                  */ 00589000
*/*    -   INITIALIZE THE MEMBER SAVE AREA                           */ 00590000
*/*    -   EXIT IF PARMLIB NOT WANTED                                */ 00591000
*/*    -   OPEN THE PARMLIB WITH THE PROPER MEMBER NAME.  IF AN      */ 00592000
*/*        ERROR IS ENCOUNTERED, ISSUE AN ERROR MESSAGE AND EXIT     */ 00593000
*/*    -   PROCESS THE PARMS FOUND IN THE MEMBER.  NOTE THAT THEY    */ 00594000
*/*        MAY BE CONTINUED FROM ONE CARD TO THE NEXT.  THE ONLY     */ 00595000
*/*        REQUIREMENT FOR CONTINUING A CARD IS TO HAVE ', ' AFTER   */ 00596000
*/*        THE LAST PARAMETER ON THE CARD.  THE NEXT CARD CAN START  */ 00597000
*/*        ANYPLACE.                                                 */ 00598000
*/*    -   CLOSE PARMLIB                                             */ 00599000
*/*    -   MAKE ANY CONSISTENCY CHECKS THAT ARE NEEDED               */ 00600000
*/*                                                                  */ 00601000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 00602000
*                                                                  0295 00603000
*   SAVEMBR=SAVES2;                 /* INITIALIZE WORK AREA          */ 00604000
         MVC   SAVEMBR(208),SAVES2                                 0295 00605000
*   IF MLPMRLIB='0'B THEN           /* SHOULD WE READ PARMLIB        */ 00606000
         TM    MLPMRLIB(MLPMPTR),B'00000100'                       0296 00607000
         BZ    @RT00296                                            0296 00608000
*     RETURN;                       /* NO - EXIT                     */ 00609000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0298 00610000
*    (R15) RESTRICTED;                                             0298 00611000
*   GEN(RDJFCB PARMLIB)             /* READ THE JFCB INTO CORE       */ 00612000
*   REFS(R0,R1,R14,R15,PARMLIB);                                   0299 00613000
         RDJFCB PARMLIB                                                 00614000
*   IF R15=4 THEN                   /* GOOD READ                     */ 00615000
         C     R15,@CF00063                                        0300 00616000
         BNE   @RF00300                                            0300 00617000
*     DO;                           /* NO                            */ 00618000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0302 00619000

*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0462 01056000
OVERLAY  ST    @14,12(,@13)                                        0462 01057000
*                                                                  0463 01058000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01059000
*/*                                                                  */ 01060000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE BUILDS A TABLE OF PARM VALUES THAT MAY BE     */ 01061000
*/*    USED TO UPDATE THE TCAS TABLE.  NOTE THAT THE TABLE 'DEFAULTS'*/ 01062000
*/*    IS DEPENDENT ON THE ORDER OF THE KEYWORD NAMES AS SET UP IN   */ 01063000
*/*    'VERIMBR'.                                                    */ 01064000
*/*                                                                  */ 01065000
*/*    THE PROCESS OF UPDATTING THE TCAS TABLE WITH NEW VALUES IS    */ 01066000
*/*    DONE IN THE FOLLOWING MANNER:                                 */ 01067000
*/*                                                                  */ 01068000
*/*    -   INITIALIZE THE BUFFER SAVE AREA (DONE IN 'SCANPARM').     */ 01069000
*/*    -   MOVE VALIDATED PARAMETERS INTO THEIR PROPER SPOT IN THE   */ 01070000
*/*        BUFFER SAVE AREA (DONE IN 'SCANPARM').                    */ 01071000
*/*    -   INITIALIZE THE MEMBER SAVE AREA (DONE IN 'READMBR').      */ 01072000
*/*    -   MOVE VALIDATED PARAMETERS INTO THEIR PROPER SPOT IN THE   */ 01073000
*/*        MEMBER SAVE AREA (DONE IN 'READMBR').                     */ 01074000
*/*    -   INITIALIZE THE MERGE AREA.  IF NO PARMLIB WAS READ, THE   */ 01075000
*/*        AREA IS NULL'ED OUT, OTHERWISE, HARD-CODED DEFAULT VALUES */ 01076000
*/*        ARE MOVED INTO THE MERGE AREA.  NOTE THAT THE MERGE AREA  */ 01077000
*/*        HAS THE SAME ORGANIZATION AS THE MEMBER SAVE AREA.        */ 01078000
*/*    -   SCAN THE MEMBER SAVE AREA.  IF A VALIDATED PARAMETER IS   */ 01079000
*/*        ENCOUNTERED, MOVE IT TO ITS PROPER SPOT IN THE MERGE AREA.*/ 01080000
*/*    -   SCAN THE BUFFER SAVE AREA.  IF A VALIDATED PARAMETER IS   */ 01081000
*/*        ENCOUNTERED, MOVE IT TO ITS PROPER SPOT IN THE MERGE AREA.*/ 01082000
*/*        NOTE THAT THE ABOVE 3 STATEMENTS IMPLY THAT OPERATOR      */ 01083000
*/*        ENTERED PARAMETERS OVERRIDE PARMLIB MEMBER PARAMETERS,    */ 01084000
*/*        WHICH IN TURN OVERRIDE HARD-CODED DEFAULTS.               */ 01085000
*/*    -   SCAN THE MERGE AREA.  IF A VALIDATED PARAMETER IS         */ 01086000
*/*        ENCOUNTERED, MOVE IT TO ITS PROPER SPOT IN THE TCAS       */ 01087000
*/*        TABLE (DONE IN 'TCASUPDT').                               */ 01088000
*/*                                                                  */ 01089000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01090000
*                                                                  0463 01091000
*   IF MLPMRLIB='0'B THEN           /* PARMLIB MEMBER READ           */ 01092000

*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01368000
*/*                                                                  */ 01369000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE PRINTS OUT ALL OF THE PARMLIB VALUES FROM THE */ 01370000
*/*    TCAS TABLE.  NOTE THAT THE CODING IS DEPENDENT ON THE ORDER   */ 01371000
*/*    OF THE KEYWORD NAMES AS SET UP IN 'VERIMBR':                  */ 01372000
*/*                                                                  */ 01373000

*/*                                                                  */ 01689000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE BUILDS UP A PRINT LINE FROM DATA FOUND IN     */ 01690000

*                                                                  0658 01694000

*PRINTIT:                                                          0682 01755000

*                                                                  0698 01805000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01806000
*/*                                                                  */ 01807000
*/*    IN ORDER TO MAKE PARAMETER VALIDATION AS INDEPENDENT AS       */ 01808000
*/*    POSSIBLE, THE ROUTINES WHICH DO THIS ARE PRIMARILY            */ 01809000
*/*    TABLE-DRIVEN.  THE MAIN TABLES WHICH ACCOMPLISH THIS ARE      */ 01810000
*/*    CALLED VERIFY TABLES ('VERIBUFR', 'VERIMBR', ETC.).  THEY     */ 01811000
*/*    CONTAIN THE CONTROL INFORMATION REGARDING EACH KEYWORD.       */ 01812000
*/*                                                                  */ 01813000
*/*    AN ELEMENT IN A VERIFY TABLE IS ORGANIZED AS FOLLOWS (SEE     */ 01814000
*/*    'SCANTBL'):                                                   */ 01815000
*/*    -   KEYWORD NAME                                              */ 01816000
*/*    -   DISPLACEMENT INDEX INTO A SAVE AREA WHERE THE VALUE       */ 01817000
*/*        ENTERED WITH THE KEYWORD NAME IS SAVED.                   */ 01818000
*/*    -   FLAGS, WHICH SHOW WHAT KIND OF EDITTING TO DO ON THE      */ 01819000
*/*        ENTERED VALUE.                                            */ 01820000
*/*    -   IF THE ENTERED VALUE HAS TO BE ONE OF A SET OF VALUES, A  */ 01821000
*/*        POINTER TO A LIST OF THE VALUES,                          */ 01822000
*/*      OR                                                          */ 01823000
*/*        A LOW NUMBER AND A HIGH NUMBER USED FOR A RANGE CHECK.    */ 01824000
*/*                                                                  */ 01825000
*/*    THE SUBROUTINES WHICH ACTUALLY DO THE VALIDATION ARE          */ 01826000
*/*    'FNDNMTCH', 'PRCSPARM', 'NBRXTRCT', AND 'REGXTRCT'.           */ 01827000
*/*                                                                  */ 01828000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01829000
*                                                                  0698 01830000
         EJECT                                                          01831000
*FNDNMTCH:                                                         0698 01832000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0698 01833000
FNDNMTCH ST    @14,12(,@13)                                        0698 01834000
*                                                                  0699 01835000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01836000
*/*                                                                  */ 01837000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE HAS TWO FUNCTIONS: 1) SCAN A BUFFER LOOKING   */ 01838000
*/*    FOR A KEYWORD NAME, AND 2) MATCH THAT KEYWORD NAME AGAINST THE*/ 01839000
*/*    ENTRIES IN A TABLE.  UPON ENTRY, 'SCANPTR' SHOULD POINT AT THE*/ 01840000
*/*    BUFFER TO BE SCANNED, AND 'TABLEPTR' SHOULD POINT AT THE      */ 01841000
*/*    TABLE USED FOR MATCHING.  UPON EXIT, 'SCANPTR' WILL POINT AT  */ 01842000
*/*    THE FIRST CHARACTER PAST THE '=' SIGN, 'WORKPARM' WILL        */ 01843000
*/*    CONTAIN THE KEYWORD NAME LEFT-JUSTIFIED AND BLANK-FILLED, AND */ 01844000
*/*    'TABLEPTR' WILL POINT AT EITHER THE MATCHING TABLE ENTRY, OR  */ 01845000
*/*    THE END OF THE TABLE IF NO MATCH WAS FOUND.                   */ 01846000
*/*                                                                  */ 01847000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01848000
*                                                                  0699 01849000
*   WORKPARM=BLANK;                 /* BLANK OUT WORK AREA           */ 01850000

*   I=0;                            /* ZERO OUT COUNTER MOVE KEYWORD    01852000
*                                      NAME INTO WORK AREA, AND ALSO    01853000
*                                      CHECK ITS LENGTH              */ 01854000
         SLR   I,I                                                 0700 01855000
*   DO WHILE(WORKCHARÂ¬='='&WORKCHARÂ¬=' '&WORKCHARÂ¬=',');           0701 01856000
         B     @DE00701                                            0701 01857000
@DL00701 DS    0H                                                  0702 01858000
*     I=I+1;                                                       0702 01859000
         AL    I,@CF00057                                          0702 01860000
*     IF I<9 THEN                                                  0703 01861000
         C     I,@CF00069                                          0703 01862000
         BNL   @RF00703                                            0703 01863000
*       WORKPRM(I)=WORKCHAR;                                       0704 01864000
         LA    @04,WORKPRM-1(I)                                    0704 01865000
         MVC   0(1,@04),WORKCHAR(SCANPTR)                          0704 01866000
*     SCANPTR=SCANPTR+1;                                           0705 01867000
@RF00703 AL    SCANPTR,@CF00057                                    0705 01868000
*   END;                                                           0706 01869000
@DE00701 CLI   WORKCHAR(SCANPTR),C'='                              0706 01870000
         BE    @DC00701                                            0706 01871000
         CLI   WORKCHAR(SCANPTR),C' '                              0706 01872000
         BE    @DC00701                                            0706 01873000
         CLI   WORKCHAR(SCANPTR),C','                              0706 01874000
         BNE   @DL00701                                            0706 01875000
@DC00701 DS    0H                                                  0707 01876000
*   IF I=0|                         /* ERROR IN                      */ 01877000
*       I>8|                        /* LENGTH OR                     */ 01878000
*       WORKCHAR=' '|               /* ENDING                        */ 01879000
*       WORKCHAR=',' THEN           /* CHARACTER                     */ 01880000
         LTR   I,I                                                 0707 01881000
         BZ    @RT00707                                            0707 01882000

         BNE   @RF00707                                            0707 01888000
@RT00707 DS    0H                                                  0708 01889000
*     DO;                           /* YES                           */ 01890000
*       SCANERR='1'B;               /* SHOW ERROR                    */ 01891000

*       RETURN;                     /* EXIT                          */ 01893000
@EL00013 DS    0H                                                  0710 01894000
@EF00013 DS    0H                                                  0710 01895000
@ER00013 L     @14,12(,@13)                                        0710 01896000
         BR    @14                                                 0710 01897000
*     END;                                                         0711 01898000
*   ELSE                            /* NO                            */ 01899000
*     SCANPTR=SCANPTR+1;            /* POINT PAST '=' SIGN SCAN TABLE   01900000
*                                      LOOKING FOR A MATCH, OR THE 0712 01901000
*                                      END OF THE TABLE              */ 01902000
@RF00707 AL    SCANPTR,@CF00057                                    0712 01903000
*   DO WHILE(TBLNAME1Â¬='FF'X&TBLNAMEÂ¬=WORKPARM);                   0713 01904000

*PRCSPARM:                                                         0719 01923000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0719 01924000
PRCSPARM ST    @14,@SA00014                                        0719 01925000
*                                                                  0720 01926000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01927000
*/*                                                                  */ 01928000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE WILL VERIFY THAT THE PARAMETER FOLLOWING A    */ 01929000
*/*    KEYWORD NAME IS A LEGAL PARAMETER.  UPON ENTRY, 'SCANPTR'     */ 01930000
*/*    SHOULD POINT TO THE FIRST CHARACTER OF THE PARAMETER,         */ 01931000
*/*    'TABLEPTR' SHOULD POINT AT THE TABLE ENTRY WE WILL USE FOR    */ 01932000
*/*    VALIDATION, AND 'SAVEPTR' SHOULD POINT AT TABLE WHICH WILL BE */ 01933000
*/*    USED TO SAVE THE EDITED AND VERIFIED PARAMETER.               */ 01934000
*/*    UPON EXIT, 'SCANPTR' WILL POINT AT THE CHARACTER WHICH STOPPED*/ 01935000
*/*    THE SCANNING OF THE PARAMETER, 'TABLEPTR' WILL BE UNCHANGED,  */ 01936000
*/*    AND 'SAVEPTR' WILL POINT AT THE SAVE AREA WHERE THE EDITED    */ 01937000
*/*    AND VERIFIED PARAMETER IS.  NOTES: - IF THE PARAMETER IS      */ 01938000
*/*    INVALID, THE FIRST BYTE OF THE SAVE AREA WILL BE 'FF'X.       */ 01939000
*/*                                       - IF MORE THAN ONE         */ 01940000
*/*    PARAMETER IS ENTERED FOR A SINGLE KEYWORD, THEN THAT          */ 01941000
*/*    KEYWORD WILL BE FLAGGED AS AN ERROR, WITH THE EXCEPTION OF    */ 01942000
*/*    THE 'RCFBDUMP' KEYWORD.                                       */ 01943000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 01944000
*                                                                  0720 01945000

*NBRXTRCT:                                                         0781 02117000
*   PROC OPTIONS(SAVE(14));                                        0781 02118000

*                                                                  0782 02120000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 02121000
*/*                                                                  */ 02122000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE MOVES A PARAMETER INTO A WORKAREA, VERIFIES   */ 02123000
*/*    THAT IT IS NUMERIC, AND CHECKS ITS LENGTH.                    */ 02124000
*/*                                                                  */ 02125000
*/*  *****************************************************************/ 02126000
*                                                                  0782 02127000
*   I=0;                            /* ZERO OUT LENGTH COUNTER       */ 02128000
         SLR   I,I                                                 0782 02129000

*/*  *****************************************************************/ 02373000
*/*                                                                  */ 02374000
*/*    THIS SUBROUTINE MOVES THE PARMS ENTERED FOR EACH KEYWORD INTO */ 02375000

         MVI   SYNADSW1,C'Y'       TURN SW ON                           02984000
         RETURN                                                         02985000

         MVI   DCBABSW1,C'Y'      SHOW EXIT ENTERED                     02987000
         TM    3(1),B'00000100'   IGNORE BIT ON                         02988000
         BZ    *+12               NO                                    02989000

         MVI   3(1),0             ACCEPT ABEND                          02992000

./  ADD  SSI=83341874,NAME=IKTCAS55
         TITLE 'IKTCAS55-- ESTAE EXIT ROUTINE'                          00001000
IKTCAS55 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00002000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00003000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00004000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00005000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00006000
         DC    C'IKTCAS55  78.336'                                 0001 00007000
         DROP  @15                                                      00008000
@PROLOG  DS    0H                                                  0002 00009000
         BALR  R15,0                                                    00010000
         USING *,R15                                                    00011000
         C     R0,INDSDWA            TEST IS THERE SDWA                 00012000
         BNE   YSDWA                 BR IF YES -R0 NOT 12               00013000
         B     START                 BR AROUND NO SDWA                  00014000
INDSDWA  DC    F'12'                 CODE 12 MEANS NO SDWA              00015000
YSDWA    STM   R14,R12,12(R13)       SAVE REGS IN SDWA                  00016000
         L     R2,0(R1)              R1 PTR ADDR OF PARAMETER           00017000
START    BALR  R12,0                 R12 BASE REG                       00018000
         USING *,R12                                                    00019000
         USING @DATD-4,R2             R2 PTR PARAMETR PASSED FROM       00020000
*                                     TASK AND R2+4 IS WORK AREA FOR    00021000
*                                     ESTAE WHICH MAY BE USED FOR       00022000
*                                     AUTO DATA                         00023000
*      ETWAWA=''B ;                    /* CLEAR THE WORK AREA        */ 00024000
         XC    ETWAWA(48,R2),ETWAWA(R2)                            0036 00025000
*      STM(R0,R2,SAVE) ;               /* SAVE REGISTERS 0,1,2       */ 00026000
         STM   R0,R2,SAVE                                          0037 00027000
*      SAVER(4)=R14  ;                 /* SAVE RETURN REG            */ 00028000
         ST    R14,SAVER+12                                        0038 00029000
*      TWAPTR=ETWATWA ;                /* TWA ADDRESSIBILITY         */ 00030000
         L     TWAPTR,ETWATWA(,R2)                                 0039 00031000
*/*                                                                  */ 00032000
*/*      VALIDITY CHECK THE ID OF TASK PASSED IN PARAMETER           */ 00033000
*/*                                                                  */ 00034000
*      IF ETWAIDÂ¬='MAIN'               /* IF IT IS NOT MAIN TASK     */ 00035000
*         THEN IF ETWAIDÂ¬='VTAM'       /* IF IT IS NOT VTAM INT TASK */ 00036000
         CLC   ETWAID(4,R2),@CC00302                               0040 00037000
         BE    @RF00040                                            0040 00038000
*           THEN IF ETWAIDÂ¬='USER'     /* IF IT IS NOT USER INT TASK */ 00039000
         CLC   ETWAID(4,R2),@CC00303                               0041 00040000
         BE    @RF00041                                            0041 00041000
*             THEN IF ETWAIDÂ¬='COMM'   /* IF IT IS NOT CON COMM TASK */ 00042000
         CLC   ETWAID(4,R2),@CC00304                               0042 00043000
         BE    @RF00042                                            0042 00044000
*               THEN DO ;              /* THEN ABEND                 */ 00045000
         CLC   ETWAID(4,R2),@CC00305                               0043 00046000
         BE    @RF00043                                            0043 00047000
*                 R1=RCABEND ;         /* SET ABEND INDICATOR        */ 00048000
         SLR   R1,R1                                               0045 00049000
*                 CALL RTNR;           /* THE ROUTINE PROCESS RETURN */ 00050000
         BAL   @14,RTNR                                            0046 00051000
*                 END ;                                            0047 00052000
*    /*                                                              */ 00053000
*    /*        CHECK AND ESTABLISH RETRY CRITERIOR THAT IS:          */ 00054000
*    /*          1 RETRY ADDR SPECIFIED IN FOOTPRINTS                */ 00055000
*    /*          2 NO PREVIOUS RETRY RECORDS FOR THIS ROUTINE        */ 00056000
*    /*                                                              */ 00057000
*      DO INDEX=4 TO 2 BY -1           /* PIN POINT THE LAST FTPRINT */ 00058000
*         WHILE(ETWAEIFC(INDEX)=0);    /* WHICH CONTAIN THE FUNCTION */ 00059000
@RF00043 DS    0H                                                  0048 00060000
@RF00042 DS    0H                                                  0048 00061000
@RF00041 DS    0H                                                  0048 00062000
@RF00040 LA    INDEX,4                                             0048 00063000
@DL00048 LR    @06,INDEX                                           0048 00064000
         SLA   @06,3                                               0048 00065000
         SLR   @03,@03                                             0048 00066000
         IC    @03,ETWAEIFC-8(@06,R2)                              0048 00067000
         C     @03,@CF00150                                        0048 00068000
         BNE   @DC00048                                            0048 00069000
*      END ;                           /* CODE                       */ 00070000
         BCTR  INDEX,0                                             0049 00071000
         C     INDEX,@CF00073                                      0049 00072000
         BNL   @DL00048                                            0049 00073000
@DC00048 DS    0H                                                  0050 00074000
*      IF ETWAEIFC(INDEX)Â¬=0           /* IF THERE IS FUNCTION CODE  */ 00075000
*         THEN DO ;                    /* THEN FURTHER CHECKING      */ 00076000
         SLR   @06,@06                                             0050 00077000
         LR    @03,INDEX                                           0050 00078000
         SLA   @03,3                                               0050 00079000
         SLR   @15,@15                                             0050 00080000
         IC    @15,ETWAEIFC-8(@03,R2)                              0050 00081000
         CR    @06,@15                                             0050 00082000
         BE    @RF00050                                            0050 00083000
*         IF ETWAERA(INDEX)Â¬=0         /* IF RETRY ADDR SPECIFIED    */ 00084000
*            THEN DO ;                 /* FURTHER CHECKING           */ 00085000
         L     @15,ETWAERA-9(@03,R2)                               0052 00086000
         LA    @15,0(,@15)                                         0052 00087000
         LTR   @15,@15                                             0052 00088000
         BZ    @RF00052                                            0052 00089000
*             IF ETWAERRS(INDEX)Â¬=0    /* IF REG SAVE AREA ADDR VALID*/ 00090000
*                THEN DO ;             /* FURTHER CHECKING           */ 00091000
         C     @06,ETWAERRS-8(@03,R2)                              0054 00092000
         BE    @RF00054                                            0054 00093000
*                DO R8=1 TO 7              /* CHECK RETRY RECORD AREA*/ 00094000
*                   WHILE(ETWARTFC(R8) /*     IF THERE IS A MATCH,   */ 00095000
*                    Â¬= ETWAEIFC(INDEX)) ; /* MEANS RETRIED BEFORE   */ 00096000
         LA    R8,1                                                0056 00097000
@DL00056 LR    @06,INDEX                                           0056 00098000
         SLA   @06,3                                               0056 00099000
         SLR   @03,@03                                             0056 00100000
         IC    @03,ETWARTFC-1(R8,R2)                               0056 00101000
         SLR   @15,@15                                             0056 00102000
         IC    @15,ETWAEIFC-8(@06,R2)                              0056 00103000
         CR    @03,@15                                             0056 00104000
         BE    @DC00056                                            0056 00105000
*                END ;                                             0057 00106000
         AL    R8,@CF00062                                         0057 00107000
         C     R8,@CF00064                                         0057 00108000
         BNH   @DL00056                                            0057 00109000
@DC00056 DS    0H                                                  0058 00110000
*                IF R8>= 8             /* IF NO MATCH                */ 00111000
*                   THEN DO ;          /* PROCESS RETRY              */ 00112000
         C     R8,@CF00060                                         0058 00113000
         BL    @RF00058                                            0058 00114000
*                   DO R8=1 TO 7             /* FIND AN AVAILABLE    */ 00115000
*                     WHILE(ETWARTFC(R8)     /* SLOT IN RETRY RECORD */ 00116000
*                           Â¬=0);            /* AREA                 */ 00117000
         LA    R8,1                                                0060 00118000
@DL00060 SLR   @06,@06                                             0060 00119000
         IC    @06,ETWARTFC-1(R8,R2)                               0060 00120000
         C     @06,@CF00150                                        0060 00121000
         BE    @DC00060                                            0060 00122000
*                   END ;                                          0061 00123000
         AL    R8,@CF00062                                         0061 00124000
         C     R8,@CF00064                                         0061 00125000
         BNH   @DL00060                                            0061 00126000
@DC00060 DS    0H                                                  0062 00127000
*                ETWARTFC(R8)=ETWAEIFC(INDEX) ;/* RECORD RETRY       */ 00128000
         LR    @06,INDEX                                           0062 00129000
         SLA   @06,3                                               0062 00130000
         SLR   @03,@03                                             0062 00131000
         IC    @03,ETWAEIFC-8(@06,R2)                              0062 00132000
         STC   @03,ETWARTFC-1(R8,R2)                               0062 00133000
*                R1=RCRETRY ;          /* RETRY INDICATOR            */ 00134000
         LA    R1,4                                                0063 00135000
*                CALL RTNR  ;          /* TO PROCESS RETURN          */ 00136000
         BAL   @14,RTNR                                            0064 00137000
*                   END ;                                          0065 00138000
*                END ;                                             0066 00139000
*            END ;                                                 0067 00140000
*         END ;                                                    0068 00141000
*         ELSE ETWAEIFC(INDEX)=DUMMYFC;/* NO FUNCTION CODE IN FTPRINT*/ 00142000
         B     @RC00050                                            0069 00143000
@RF00050 LR    @06,INDEX                                           0069 00144000

         LR    SAVREG,14     LOAD RETURN ADDRESS INTO SAVE REGISTER     00019000

./  ADD  SSI=83341879,NAME=IKTXLOG
         TITLE 'EXTENDED LOGON ROUTINE'                                 00001000
IKTXLOG  CSECT ,                                                   0001 00002000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00003000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00004000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00005000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00006000
         DC    C'IKTXLOG   78.336'                                 0001 00007000
         DROP  @15                                                      00008000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00009000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00010000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00011000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00012000
*   INBUF=TVWAVST;                  /* INSERT ADDRESS OF LOGON BUFFER   00013000
*                                      IN PARAMETER                  */ 00014000
         L     @15,BASEPTR(,REG1)                                  0019 00015000
         L     @14,ASCBPTR                                         0019 00016000
         L     @14,TSBPTR(,@14)                                    0019 00017000
         L     @14,TSBEXTNT(,@14)                                  0019 00018000
         L     @14,TVWAPTR(,@14)                                   0019 00019000
         L     @00,TVWAVST(,@14)                                   0019 00020000
         ST    @00,INBUF(,@15)                                     0019 00021000
*   END IKTXLOG                                                    0020 00022000
*                                                                  0020 00023000
*/* THE FOLLOWING INCLUDE STATEMENTS WERE FOUND IN THIS PROGRAM.     */ 00024000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IHAPSA  )                                       */ 00025000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IHAASCB )                                       */ 00026000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IKJTSB  )                                       */ 00027000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IKTTSBX )                                       */ 00028000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IKTTVWA )                                       */ 00029000
*                                                                  0020 00030000
*       ;                                                          0020 00031000
@EL00001 DS    0H                                                  0020 00032000
@EF00001 DS    0H                                                  0020 00033000
@ER00001 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0020 00034000
         BR    @14                                                 0020 00035000
@DATA    DS    0H                                                       00036000
@DATD    DSECT                                                          00037000
         DS    0F                                                       00038000
IKTXLOG  CSECT                                                          00039000
         DS    0F                                                       00040000
@DATD    DSECT                                                          00041000
         DS    0D                                                       00042000
@ENDDATD EQU   *                                                        00043000
IKTXLOG  CSECT                                                          00044000
         NOPR  ((@ENDDATD-@DATD)*16)                                    00045000
         DS    0F                                                       00046000
@SIZDATD DC    AL1(0)                                                   00047000
         DC    AL3(@ENDDATD-@DATD)                                      00048000
         DS    0D                                                       00049000
@00      EQU   00                      EQUATES FOR REGISTERS 0-15       00050000

*TSBCLEAN: PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVEAREA,NOSAVE);                        0105 00087000
TSBCLEAN DS    0H                                                  0106 00088000
*/*                                                                  */ 00089000
*/********************************************************************/ 00090000
*/*                                                                  */ 00091000
*/*                 TSBCLEAN IS AN INTERNAL PROC THAT CLEANS UP      */ 00092000
*/*             THE TSB ASSOCIATED WITH THE TPUT/TGET.               */ 00093000
*/*             FOR A TGET, NOTHING IS NECESSARY                     */ 00094000
*/*             FOR A TPUT TO THE TERMINAL ASSOCIATED WITH THIS      */ 00095000
*/*             ADDRESS SPACE, STATUS IS CALLED TO RE-DISPATCH       */ 00096000
*/*             WAITING TASKS IF THEY ARE WAITING ON THE TASK, AND   */ 00097000
*/*             TSB FIELDS ARE CLEARED.                              */ 00098000
*/*             FOR AN ASID TPUT, THE CSA AREAS ARE FREED IF THE     */ 00099000
*/*             DESTINATION TERMINAL HAS RELINQUISHED CONTROL OF     */ 00100000
*/*             THE AREAS....  IF THE DESTINATION HAS NOT            */ 00101000
*/*             RELINQUISHED CONTROL, THEN THIS TASK INDICATES THAT  */ 00102000
*/*             IT DOES,SO THAT THE DESTINATION WILL FREE THE AREAS  */ 00103000
*/*         ****TSBCLEAN SAVES RETURN ADDRESS IN XSASAVEA            */ 00104000
*/*                                                                  */ 00105000
*/********************************************************************/ 00106000
*/*                                                                 **/ 00107000
*RFY RTNREG RSTD;                                                  0106 00108000
*XSASAVEA = RTNREG;                  /* SAVE RETURN ADDRESS         **/ 00109000
         ST    RTNREG,XSASAVEA(,RBSECPTR)                          0107 00110000
*RFY RTNREG UNRSTD;                                                0108 00111000
*/********************************************************************/ 00112000
*/*      OBTAIN LOCAL LOCK                                           */ 00113000
*/********************************************************************/ 00114000
*                                                                  0109 00115000
*GEN SETS(RTNREG,ENTRYREG,REG0,REG1) REFS(PSALITA,FLC);            0109 00116000
         SETLOCK OBTAIN,TYPE=LOCAL,MODE=UNCOND,REGS=USE,              --00117000
               RELATED=(TSB,TSBCLEAN(RETURN))                           00118000
*IF TSBPTR Â¬= 0 & TSBCTCB =CURNTTCB THEN /* IF FOREGROUND JOB, THEN     00119000
*                                           DOES THIS TASK 'OWN'   0110 00120000
*                                           THE TSB ?               **/ 00121000
         SLR   @08,@08                                             0110 00122000
         CR    TSBPTR,@08                                          0110 00123000
         BE    @RF00110                                            0110 00124000
         L     @07,CVTPTR                                          0110 00125000
         L     @04,CVTTCBP(,@07)                                   0110 00126000
         CLC   TSBCTCB(4,TSBPTR),CURNTTCB(@04)                     0110 00127000
         BNE   @RF00110                                            0110 00128000
*  DO;                                                             0111 00129000
*    TSBOWIP = '0'B;                 /* CLEAR 'OWAIT IN PROGRESS     */ 00130000
         NI    TSBOWIP(TSBPTR),B'11011111'                         0112 00131000
*    TSBCTCB =  0;                   /* SET TO NOT 'OWN' TSB         */ 00132000
         ST    @08,TSBCTCB(,TSBPTR)                                0113 00133000
*    /*                                                              */ 00134000
*    /*    CALL STATUS TO RE-DISPATCH TASKS WAITING ON THIS          */ 00135000
*    /*    TASK TO COMPLETE TPUT PROCESSING.                         */ 00136000
*    /*                                                              */ 00137000

*FREESTOR: PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVEAREA,NOSAVE);                        0160 00311000

*/*                                                                  */ 00313000
*/********************************************************************/ 00314000
*/*                                                                  */ 00315000
*/*      FREESTOR ASSURES THAT A CROSS-MEMORY POST IS COMPLETE       */ 00316000
*/*      AND THEN FREES THE CSA AREAS THAT WERE ALLOCATED FOR        */ 00317000
*/*      THE SRB AND THE DATA AREA. BOTH AREAS ARE FREED USING       */ 00318000
*/*      THE GLOBAL,BRANCH ENTRY                                     */ 00319000
*/*      LOCAL LOCK IS NOT HELD                                      */ 00320000
*/*   **** THE RETURN ADDRESS IS STORED IN XSASAVEB                  */ 00321000
*/*                                                                  */ 00322000

*/*                                                                  */ 00324000

*/********************************************************************/ 00396000
